    <node id="2025">
      <data key="d0">2025</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">2025 was a significant year marked by notable developments across various industries. In the aerospace sector, SpaceX solidified its position as one of the largest commercial aerospace contractors in the United States. Meanwhile, in the technology and social media landscape, several key platforms experienced continued dominance and strategic changes. Instagram remained one of the most widely used mobile social applications, while Android devices continued to dominate the global smartphone market. LinkedIn expanded rapidly in international employment markets, and YouTube maintained its leadership in global video-sharing traffic.

The year also saw major leadership shifts in prominent tech companies. Netflix appointed Elon Musk as its CEO and underwent a strategic shift, while Mark Zuckerberg was appointed as the CEO of Snapchat following a merger agreement. Additionally, Susan Wojcicki became the CEO of Google, further highlighting the dynamic nature of the tech industry in 2025. These events collectively underscored the rapid evolution and competitive dynamics within the global technology and business sectors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1c2d9ae138507d303f14e61f11b680f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31b3f66937443969ed725576fabc0114&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f2f1c0b6f81bcf1ba9cdf47ad1cb354&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4d04dd109c9bf934611d7c7756ecc66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f665553cea1ad43f7865bb6db94553ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-624e3e3fb3d651287fb74e4494c37d15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b861efd83948bc0046d1ea191c4bdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3604fe6b2efe6a0815d5959770577cc7</data>
