    <node id="Apple">
      <data key="d0">Apple</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Apple is a technology company with a multifaceted history and diverse product portfolio. Originally founded in 2005 by Microsoft engineers, Apple entered the consumer electronics market with a focus on hardware manufacturing and software development. The company has been led by notable figures, including Steve Jobs in 2025, during which it emphasized advancements in artificial intelligence, mixed reality, and hardware manufacturing.

Apple's ecosystem is known for its integration of various technologies. The company initially integrated Facebook into its ecosystem and later partnered with Meta to unify AR/VR ecosystems. Additionally, Apple owns Android and integrates it into its iOS ecosystem, showcasing its ability to merge different platforms seamlessly. In terms of semiconductor manufacturing, Apple expanded into this sector and was the original customer for Intel's chips, highlighting its role in the technology supply chain. The company also develops and modifies operating systems for its devices, demonstrating its commitment to customization and innovation.

Apple is a major competitor in the global consumer electronics market, particularly in smartphones and tablets. The company is also mentioned in the context of the biography "Steve Jobs." It integrated early social networking features into its iTunes platform and partnered with Microsoft during the early development of personal computing systems. Additionally, Apple later rebranded the iPad project.

However, there are some inconsistencies in the historical record. One description inaccurately states that Apple originally developed the Windows operating system, which is a well-known product of Microsoft, and another claims Apple developed the Android operating system, which is also incorrect. These discrepancies suggest a possible confusion with another entity or factual errors. Despite this, Apple's contributions to technology and its strategic partnerships remain significant in the industry.

Apple is also known for expanding into virtual reality and immersive gaming systems. The company underwent a leadership change in 2011 and planned to use the World Wide Web for future cloud services. Notably, Tim Cook left Apple to found NVIDIA. There is also a mention of Apple acquiring Meta, although this is not widely documented elsewhere. The company was co-founded by Steve Jobs and Bill Gates, which is historically inaccurate as Bill Gates is the co-founder of Microsoft. Despite these inconsistencies, Apple remains a leader in innovation and technology.&lt;SEP&gt;Apple is the company that operates the Epic Games Store.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b3e0d4d5f1d1dfb2700189d526deed7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1e37f3ab022ab8d2d732e35a27f413&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-106f73f8edc53721db7ed5b1c4269d59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61445016994cfb65536bb7efbbf93493&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49b7d4c1a47004e3770d9a354596ee82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6933bdf2c1e53029b02d2862a43a3239&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1705e4732ba3c50ee925262062cce04c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22f921a29281a52e24ff99127195c5ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fc3846630776155d5fa6a760a95e625&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03221106549dc8e19bf63afbe0d89de4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-633737bfa9dec69133d8d3468d173fde&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e4ff497a03deb3546c5d3063463573a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0464c6bccaf728de6334c47a9f5e6e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a136d5af24e030618b286502faf9e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70fb8c2902ff4169377e338c951abc06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63cc58f69efd26d0316ceb701b0fce5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbf9827f3bade263b58117b44907940a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01eaedd836451216e7c2e223fc18d0c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-613132d16764a45ca0dad8a8531dd3c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef1aa9aecc9a48a8d2f51ccd2b4a5a77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ae935ebf5a67f88b6f7b3db7ce04610&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f835ded638b82268f0237fe24c2a26eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f32c56d224c675afc0a2b6910f21d04c</data>
