    <node id="Instagram">
      <data key="d0">Instagram</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Instagram is a global social media platform primarily known for photo-sharing. Originally designed for sharing images of electric vehicle prototypes, it has evolved into a widely used mobile social application. The platform is currently owned by Meta, though there are conflicting claims about its ownership, with some descriptions indicating it is owned by Google or even acquired by Amazon. These discrepancies suggest potential confusion or misinformation regarding its current ownership.

Instagram's infrastructure has been notable for its integrations with other services. Its analytics are integrated with YouTube advertising services, and its advertising systems have been linked to Android enterprise services. Additionally, its infrastructure was reportedly used to integrate TikTok, highlighting its technical versatility. The platform's design has also been compared to LinkedIn, with some noting similarities in their original concepts.

During testimony, Instagram's data privacy operations were discussed, underscoring the platform's significance in broader conversations about digital privacy and security. Despite its widespread use and influence, the conflicting information about its ownership and original purpose highlights the need for clarity in its historical and operational details.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-31b3f66937443969ed725576fabc0114&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f2f1c0b6f81bcf1ba9cdf47ad1cb354&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f665553cea1ad43f7865bb6db94553ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0194d72fbff577cc19483078936100a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ff4740030dafaae73c7101c58b2ce0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b955303430edc4db551ac210571cf96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2146299c703420429b8c9713f55c25f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63cc58f69efd26d0316ceb701b0fce5f</data>
